node.text:
Today, FPC announced a lawsuit against Nevada Governor Steve Sisolak. The suit was filed in response to the governor's signing of AB 286, a bill that establishes a new, confiscatory ban on all unserialized, self-manufactured firearms as well as all “unfinished frames or receivers.” FPC Attorney Bill Sack explains how the bill seeks to limit your right to keep and bear arms, as well as explains how you can take action and help fight this unconstitutional legislation.

To help support FPC in this, and many other efforts to protect and expand the right to keep and bear arms, please consider joining the FPC Grassroots Army by visiting JoinFPC.org

node.title: FPC files lawsuit against Nevada's AB 286 banning home built firearms

FPC's Matt Larosiere sits down and explains the ins and outs of the ATF's Proposed Rule 2021R-08, a rule change which would all but ban the legal use of pistol braces. The new rule contains a huge degree of vague and uncertain principles, combined with an absurd and illogical "points system" and a clause giving the ATF power to rule against their own criteria if they so choose!

This new rule is a slap in the face of gun owners, and we can't afford for it to go into effect. Unfortunately, the ATF is not yet allowing comments on their new proposed rule – though comments will open in the near future. To stay up-to-date, and to take action once comments are live, please visit SaveTheBraces.com. The ATF has just released Proposed Rule 2021R-08, which would reclassify millions of braced pistols as NFA-defined Short Barrel Rifles (SBRs). Much like the ATF's new receiver rule (2021R-05), this new rule greatly expands ATF power at the expense of your right to keep and bear arms. Furthermore, this new rule would make millions of law-abiding gun owners into felons overnight, thanks to backroom administrative lawmaking.

While the ATF announced the rule today, they have no yet opened the rule for comment. Stay tuned to SaveTheBraces.com for the most up-to-date news, where we will include a link to comment on the proposed rule as soon as the ATF publishes it. While you're at it, please also visit FightATF.com to fight back against the ATF's propsed rule on braces, and FightChipman.com to demand your senator vote "No" on Waco Dave's nomination to lead the corrupt ATF.
